sub_title: Head of Welfare at ONCAMPUS Global
summary:
Enthusiastic and experienced educator and wellbeing facilitator, with excellent communication and interpersonal skills, honed through my professional and personal experience.

Ability to motivate, empower and inspire people in an international education environment.

Highly adaptable to new environments, sensitive to other cultures, empathetic, considerate and compassionate.

Deep personal interest in mental health, human rights and refugee issues with knowledge regarding those gained through voluntary work, UNHCR and Amnesty International internships, educational workshops organised and completed in Poland, Germany, the UK and the Netherlands, preparation of master thesis and numerous books read in my free time.
